    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Raikes</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">Personal.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chargé</hi>: Confirming my note to you of the
                    22d ultimo, I now take pleasure in quoting what follows from a report made by
                    the commanding officer of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Cincinnati</hi> at La
                    Guaira and forwarded by the Secretary of the Navy on the 2d instant: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Having learned that a British subject was being held in involuntary
                            service in the revolutionary army, I requested the general, Pablo
                            Guzman, to release him, which was done.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
